					<h1>Guidance Practices </h1>
					<h2>&quot;Significant Guidance Documents:&quot; Agency Good Guidance Practices</h2>
					<p> To improve the quality, transparency, accountability, and coordination of the use of guidance documents by Federal agencies, the President issued Executive Order (EO) 13422, &ldquo;Amendment to Executive Order 12866 for Regulatory Planning and Review,&rdquo; on January 18, 2007. EO 13422 clarified the Office of Management and Budget&rsquo;s (OMB) authority to oversee agency guidance practices. On that same day, OMB issued the Final Bulletin on Agency Good Guidance Practices (the Bulletin), which establishes policies and procedures for agencies to apply in their development and issuance of &ldquo;significant&rdquo; and &ldquo;economically significant&rdquo; guidance documents, as defined by OMB. </p>
					<p><a href="/guidance/docs/OMB_FedReg_good_guidance.pdf" target="_blank"> Final Bulletin for Agency Good Guidance Practices</a> &nbsp;(PDF)<br>
					</p>
					<p> OIG currently has no significant guidance documents, as defined in EO 13422 and the Bulletin. Requests for the issuance of &ldquo;significant guidance documents&rdquo; may be submitted electronically below. Any future such documents issued by OIG will appear on a list here. </p>
					<p> Comments pertaining to OIG guidance designated as &ldquo;significance guidance documents&rdquo; and/or requests for their issuance, reconsideration, modification, or rescission may be submitted to OIG at <a href="mailto:public.affairs@oig.hhs.gov">public.affairs@oig.hhs.gov</a>. </p>
					<p> Please note that all of OIG&rsquo;s guidance can be located as previously organized on <a href="/"> OIG&rsquo;s Web site</a>. </p>
					<p> If you believe that OIG is not complying with the Bulletin, you may contact <a href="mailto:public.affairs@oig.hhs.gov">public.affairs@oig.hhs.gov</a>.</p>

